-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. DEFINITIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"Software" means the girl-agent project, including source code, binaries,
scripts, prompts, models, datasets, APIs, configuration files, documentation,
examples, assets, interfaces, names, visual identity, behavior, concepts, and
related materials.

"Project" means the original girl-agent repository, its official distribution
channels, and its maintainers.

"Maintainers" means the copyright holder, repository owner, or any person or
entity authorized by the copyright holder to maintain the Project.

"Contribution" means a bug fix, patch, pull request, issue report,
documentation improvement, translation, test, benchmark, security report,
tutorial, integration, or other work submitted in good faith for inclusion in,
or direct improvement of, the original Project.

"Contribution Purpose" means use of the Software primarily and directly for:
- studying the Software;
- testing the Software;
- reporting bugs;
- preparing patches;
- preparing pull requests;
- improving documentation;
- improving security;
- improving compatibility;
- proposing features;
- or otherwise contributing back to the original Project.

"Fork" means any copy, clone, mirror, branch, modified version, derivative work,
adaptation, remix, variant, continuation, reimplementation based substantially
on the Software, or repository derived from the Software.

"Independent Fork" means any Fork that is published, promoted, maintained,
hosted, distributed, or developed as a separate project, alternative version,
community edition, competing implementation, replacement, continuation,
successor, or substantially similar product outside the control of the original
Project.

"Derivative Work" means any modification, adaptation, remix, transformation,
extension, edited version, altered version, or substantially similar work based
on the Software, including works that change names, characters, personalities,
prompts, behavior, branding, themes, interface, assets, configuration, or other
details while preserving the core concept, structure, code, prompts,
architecture, user experience, or distinctive behavior of the Software.

"Non-Commercial Use" means personal, educational, academic, research, security
research, hobby, evaluation, and internal non-revenue-generating use that does
not primarily generate revenue or provide a commercial business service.

"Commercial Use" includes selling, licensing, paid hosting, SaaS hosting, paid
APIs, enterprise/internal business usage, monetized services, advertising-based
services, subscription services, or use of the Software as part of a commercial
product, commercial platform, or revenue-generating activity.

